title: The Motor Girls on a Tour
description: LibriVox recording of The Motor Girls on a Tour by Margaret Penrose. Read by Lucy Burgoyne. This is the second book in the series of the Motor Girls. Join Cora and her friends in this mystery and adventure of The Motor Girls. Also the search for a missing table and promise book belonging to a cripple girl called Wren. Why is Clip so mysterious? What is she up to? Is Sid Wilcox up to his old tricks with his chum Rob Roland? (Summary by Lucy Burgoyne) For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: motor girls; penrose; children; fiction; mystery; audio books; librivox;
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: but 10 hours of Lucy Burgoyne and I would pull my hair out.

I'm not rating this one in particular because I haven't listened to it yet, but I just wanted to comment that I have listened to other recording's of Lucy's, and I've enjoyed them.  I think her accent is cute (although it did take a while for me to get used to it and easily understand her) and now she sounds like an old friend to me.
